High-level feature merge

Area	CinemAi Neo (yours)	Short.ai-style add-ons	
Input	Photo, script, production packs	Hooks, ideas, templates, auto-script	
Output	Cinematic videos	Short-form cuts, variants, captions, formats	
Growth	None yet	Multi-platform posting, scheduling, analytics	
Monetization	Trips + Pro	Same, plus “Creator Pro” angle	


---

1. New feature layer: “Shorts mode”

Alongside Simple and Pro, add:

• Shorts mode:• Input options:• Text idea → “Write me a script for…”
• Long script → auto-cut into multiple shorts.
• Existing video → auto-cut best moments.

• AI does:• Generates hook-first scripts.
• Suggests 3–5 variants per idea.
• Auto-adds captions, emojis, on-screen text.

• Output formats:• 9:16 (TikTok/Reels/Shorts).
• 1:1 (feed).
• 16:9 (YouTube).




So app has 3 entry points:

• Photo + Script (Cinematic)
• Production Pack (Pro)
• Shorts (Growth)


---

2. Social + distribution features

Add a “Publish” layer on top of productions:

• Connected accounts:• TikTok, Instagram, YouTube, X, etc. (via OAuth).

• Per production:• Toggle: “Create short-form versions from this production”.
• Auto-generate:• Clips with captions.
• Suggested titles, descriptions, hashtags.


• Scheduling:• User picks:• Platforms.
• Time slots.

• Queue stored in your backend, posted via background workers.



On mobile:

• After a video is Ready:• Show button: “Create Shorts & Publish”.
• Wizard:• Choose platforms.
• Edit captions.
• Schedule or post now.




---

3. Extended data model for Short.ai-style features

Add a few tables.

Shorts & variants

• shorts• id
• production_id
• user_id
• source_type (cinema, upload, script_only)
• status (draft, queued, processing, ready)
• main_video_url
• created_at

• short_variants• id
• short_id
• hook_text
• caption_text
• hashtags
• format (9_16, 1_1, 16_9)
• video_url
• performance_score (nullable, from analytics)
• created_at



Social connections & posts

• social_accounts• id
• user_id
• platform (tiktok, instagram, youtube, x, etc.)
• handle
• access_token_encrypted
• refresh_token_encrypted
• expires_at
• created_at

• social_posts• id
• user_id
• short_variant_id
• platform
• status (scheduled, posted, failed)
• scheduled_at
• posted_at
• platform_post_id
• created_at



Analytics

• social_metrics• id
• social_post_id
• views
• likes
• comments
• shares
• watch_time_seconds
• collected_at



This lets you:

• Show per-variant performance.
• Suggest: “This hook style works best for you.”


