4. UX additions for Short.ai-style power

On Home

• Add a “Growth” section:• “This week’s posts”
• “Best performing short”
• “Suggested new hooks”



New screens

• Shorts dashboard• List of shorts grouped by:• Draft, Scheduled, Live.

• Each card shows:• Thumbnail.
• Platforms.
• Key metrics.


• Hook lab• User enters:• Niche, tone, target audience.

• AI generates:• Hook ideas.
• Full scripts.
• Option: “Turn into short now”.


• Brand kit• User sets:• Colors.
• Fonts (or font style).
• Logo.
• Lower-third style.

• AI applies this to:• Captions.
• Overlays.
• Thumbnails.




---

5. AI pipeline extension for shorts

On top of your cinema pipeline, add a shorts pipeline:

1. Idea/script generation• From user prompt or long script.
• Generate multiple hook-first scripts.

2. Shot planning• For each script:• Decide if it’s:• Talking head.
• B-roll heavy.
• Mixed.



3. Visual generation• If user has a photo/avatar:• Use it as anchor.

• Else:• Generate stylized visuals (Neo Glow, etc.).


4. Caption & layout• Auto-generate:• Word-perfect captions.
• Emphasis with emojis, bold words (visually).

• Place them in safe zones for each platform.

5. Export & variants• Render multiple aspect ratios.
• Attach suggested titles, descriptions, hashtags.

6. Publish & learn• Post via connected accounts.
• Pull metrics.
• Update performance_score.
• Feed back into “Hook lab” suggestions.



---

6. Pricing with Short.ai-style value

Your existing model still works, just add Shorts framing:

• Free:• X cinema productions/month.
• Y shorts/month.
• Limited platforms, no scheduling.

• Pro ($49/month):• More cinema productions.
• More shorts (e.g. 100–300/month).
• Scheduling + multi-platform posting.
• Brand kit.
• Analytics.

• $1 Trip:• 1 cinema production or
• A bundle of shorts (e.g. up to 5 variants from one idea).



You can later split into:

• CinemAi Pro (cinema-focused).
• Creator Pro (shorts + growth).
• Or keep it unified but message it differently.


---

7. Neo Glow UI with growth layer

Keep the same Neo Glow aesthetic, but:

• Growth cards:• Neon borders showing platform colors subtly.
• Tiny metrics row: views, likes, watch time.

• Hook lab:• Terminal-like panel with glowing cursor.
• Generated hooks appear as stacked cards you can swipe through.



---

8. How this is now “beyond CinemAi + Short.ai”

You’re combining:

• Deep production (multi-folder, contracts, code, assets).
• Cinematic output (full productions).
• Short-form growth engine (hooks, shorts, scheduling, analytics).


So the story becomes:

“Upload your world once—get full cinematic pieces and an ongoing stream of optimized shorts that auto-grow your channels.”